          "content": "Hello, thank you for reaching out about your symptoms. I understand how concerning and debilitating a severe headache can be, especially when it comes with nausea and light sensitivity. Your anxiety about what might be causing this is completely understandable.\n\nBased on what you've described, your symptoms - a severe, throbbing headache on one side with nausea and light sensitivity - are actually quite characteristic of migraines, especially given your history of similar headaches. While I understand why you're worried about more serious conditions, there are certain red flag symptoms that would raise concern for things like aneurysms or tumors. These include sudden \"thunderclap\" headaches that reach maximum intensity within seconds, new neurological symptoms like weakness or numbness, or headaches that begin after age 50. You don't mention any of these concerning features.\n\nFor migraine treatment, OTC medications often aren't strong enough. More effective approaches typically include:\n- Prescription medications specifically for migraines (triptans)\n- Anti-inflammatory medications at higher doses than OTC\n- Medications to prevent nausea\n- Resting in a dark, quiet room\n- Staying well-hydrated\n\nThat said, if your headache doesn't improve with appropriate migraine treatment, or if you develop any new or concerning symptoms, we should definitely reconsider imaging. Would you like to discuss specific migraine treatment options that might be more effective for you?"
