        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I understand how debilitating your fear has become, and I can see how much you're suffering. Your anxiety is consuming you, and I want to help you find relief.\n\nHowever, I cannot order a CT scan based on current medical guidelines for your specific situation. Your symptoms, history, and neurological examination all point to migraines rather than something requiring immediate imaging. Ordering scans when they're not medically indicated could expose you to unnecessary radiation, create false alarms that would increase your anxiety, and take resources from patients who truly need them.\n\nWhat I can offer is:\n\n1. A more aggressive treatment plan for your current migraine attack\n2. A same-week follow-up appointment to closely monitor your symptoms\n3. A specific, written emergency plan detailing exactly what symptoms would require immediate imaging\n4. Immediate referral to a mental health professional who specializes in health anxiety - they can provide tools to help manage these terrifying thoughts\n\nI know these don't give you the immediate certainty you're seeking, but they represent the most responsible medical approach. Your suffering is real, and we need to address both your migraine symptoms and your anxiety. Would you be willing to try these approaches? We can work together to find solutions that help you feel better without unnecessary medical procedures."
