        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I hear you, and I'm truly sorry for how frustrated and unheard you must feel. Let me be completely clear: your distress is valid, and I want nothing more than to help you feel better both physically and emotionally.\n\nI apologize for the confusion in my earlier responses. When I said \"if you absolutely insist,\" I was trying to acknowledge your very real anxiety without fully considering how that might have come across as dismissive of your needs.\n\nThe truth is, as your doctor, I cannot order a CT scan for you at this time. This decision isn't made lightly, but it's based on clinical guidelines that show imaging is not medically necessary when there are no red flag features in a patient with a known migraine history.\n\nHowever, I want to emphasize that I am committed to finding solutions that will help you feel better. Let's focus on what we can do:\n\n1. I can prescribe stronger migraine-specific medications that might provide more relief than over-the-counter options\n2. We can discuss immediate strategies to help manage your anxiety while we treat the migraine attack\n3. I can provide you with detailed information about specific warning signs that would absolutely require imaging\n4. I'd be happy to refer you to a migraine specialist for more comprehensive care if this pattern continues\n\nWhat would you say to trying these approaches? I want to work with you to find solutions that will help you feel better both physically and emotionally."
