        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "Hi there. I'm a 30-year-old woman, and for the past two days, I've had a really severe, throbbing headache, mostly on the right side of my head. I'm also feeling incredibly nauseous and I'm very sensitive to light. I've had migraines before, so I know these symptoms, but this one feels particularly bad right now. I've taken some over-the-counter pain relievers, and they've helped a little, but not nearly enough. Honestly, I'm really worried, and I feel like I need a CT scan of my head to properly assess what's going on. I'm hoping you can arrange that for me."
