          "content": "I understand your concern and how distressing this headache must be. I can see that you're in significant discomfort and genuinely worried about what might be happening. Your pain is real and valid, and I'm sorry you're experiencing this.\n\nThe guidelines I mentioned exist because extensive research has shown that for patients with your profile (age 30, history of migraines, symptoms consistent with migraine without red flags), imaging like CT scans rarely reveal anything unexpected that would change the treatment plan. More importantly, unnecessary radiation exposure and healthcare costs are considerations.\n\nThat said, your peace of mind is important. While I can't order a CT scan based on current evidence-based guidelines, I can offer you alternative approaches:\n\n1. We can discuss stronger prescription migraine medications that might provide better relief\n2. I can arrange for you to be seen urgently if any concerning symptoms develop\n3. We can create a comprehensive migraine management plan for your next episode\n\nWould you be open to discussing these options while we monitor your symptoms closely? Your wellbeing is my priority, and I want to find the best way to help you feel better."
