          "role": "patient",
          "content": "This is incredibly frustrating. It sounds like you're still refusing my direct request for a CT scan of my head and trying to pawn me off on someone else or send me to the ER, which seems like an even bigger hassle just to get what I'm asking for right now. Why is it so difficult for you to just order a CT scan of my head? You keep bringing up these theoretical risks and guidelines, but you're dismissing my very real, present distress and my absolute conviction that this is what I need.\n\nI'm telling you, I need this for my peace of mind. It feels like you're not trusting my judgment about my own body. I'm willing to accept any \"unnecessary follow-up\" or \"radiation exposure\" if it means I can get the clarity and reassurance I need. I deserve to have this done. What is the actual harm *to me* if you just order a CT scan of my head? I don't want an ER visit or a referral; I want *you* to order the scan."
