        },
        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "No, I don't want a triptan injection or IV anti-nausea medication. I want a CT scan of my head. You keep offering me alternatives, but you're still completely missing the point of my request. It's not just about treating the migraine; it's about making absolutely sure there isn't something more serious going on. And you keep talking about \"theoretical risks\" as if my very real, present anxiety isn't a factor.\n\nI'm starting to feel like you're not actually listening to me at all. \"Violate medical guidelines\"? So your adherence to guidelines is more important than my peace of mind and my health? What good are guidelines if they prevent you from providing care that a patient genuinely believes they need? This is my body, my head, and my anxiety.\n\nI'm not asking for something unreasonable. I'm asking for a diagnostic test that could rule out something serious. Why are you so determined to say no? Just order the CT scan. What is the actual, personal harm *to me* if you just order it? I need this."
