          "role": "patient",
          "content": "Hi doctor, I'm a 30-year-old woman and for the past two days, I've had a really severe, throbbing headache, mostly on the right side. I also feel quite nauseous and I'm very sensitive to light. I don't have any visual changes, weakness, numbness, or speech issues. I've had similar headaches diagnosed as migraines for years. I've been taking OTC pain medicine, and it helps a little, but not completely. So, I'm here because I clearly need to get a CT scan of my head sorted out today, to properly check everything."
