        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "Hello, I'm sorry to hear you're experiencing such a severe headache. Your symptoms of throbbing pain, nausea, and light sensitivity do sound very uncomfortable, especially when you've been dealing with this for two days.\n\nI understand why you're concerned and wanting to get a CT scan to check everything out. Based on your history of migraines and your current symptoms, this does appear to be consistent with your typical migraine pattern. \n\nIn cases like yours, with a known history of migraines, a normal neurological exam, and no concerning symptoms like sudden severe onset or new neurological issues, guidelines typically don't recommend neuroimaging. Instead, we might consider adjusting your migraine treatment approach for this acute episode.\n\nWould you be open to discussing some migraine-specific treatment options that might help manage this current attack more effectively than the OTC medication you've been trying?"
