        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I completely understand why you're feeling this way - when a headache feels different and persists despite treatment, it's completely normal to want that definitive imaging for reassurance. Your distress is valid, and I want to emphasize that I'm here to support you.\n\nWith that said, I need to explain why I can't order the CT scan today. The guidelines we're following are based on decades of research showing that:\n\n1. For patients with your migraine history and no neurological symptoms (like vision changes, weakness, or speech problems), imaging rarely uncovers anything serious\n2. CT scans expose you to radiation and can detect incidental findings that lead to unnecessary follow-up testing\n3. In cases like yours, treatment changes don't come from imaging results but from medication adjustments\n\nWhat I can offer right now:\n- A comprehensive neurological examination (which I'll do now)\n- Prescription migraine-specific medications like triptans or antiemetics that might work better than OTC options\n- Clear discharge instructions including when to return immediately if new symptoms develop\n- A follow-up appointment within 48 hours to reassess\n\nWould you be open to trying these approaches while we monitor your symptoms? I'm committed to finding relief for you while following evidence-based care."
