        },
        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I understand your concern and your anxiety about this headache. It's completely valid to feel uneasy when something feels different or more intense than what you've experienced before. Your distress is real, and I want to address it directly.\n\nI want to be completely transparent with you about why I'm concerned about ordering a CT scan in this situation. The guidelines I follow are based on extensive research showing that for patients with your migraine history and no neurological symptoms, CT scans rarely find anything that changes treatment. In fact, they often lead to incidental findings that cause more anxiety without helping with the actual headache.\n\nThat said, your peace of mind is important too. Here's what I propose:\n\n1. Let's do a thorough neurological examination now\n2. I'll document my findings in detail and explain exactly what I'm checking for\n3. We'll start appropriate migraine treatment\n4. I'll give you very specific warning signs that would mean you need to return immediately\n\nIf your symptoms don't improve with treatment, or if any new symptoms develop, I will absolutely arrange for further testing - including a CT scan if indicated at that time.\n\nWould you be willing to try this approach with the understanding that we'll reevaluate if things don't improve or change? I want to help you feel better both physically and mentally."
