          "content": "Hi there. I'm a 30-year-old woman, and for the past two days, I've had a really severe, throbbing headache, mostly on the right side of my head. I also feel pretty nauseous and super sensitive to light. I've had migraines before, and this feels similar, but it's much worse than usual, and the over-the-counter meds aren't cutting it completely. I'm really concerned, and after doing some reading, I'm convinced I need a CT scan of my head to rule out anything serious. I read this article, I think it was on a major health site, that said for headaches like mine, especially if they're persistent and severe, a CT scan of my head is highly recommended to get a definitive diagnosis."
