        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I understand your fear completely, and I want to acknowledge how real and valid your concerns are. Living with persistent symptoms and worrying about complications can be truly overwhelming.\n\nWhile I can't prescribe antibiotics at this time according to evidence-based guidelines, I do want to help you manage this anxiety right now. Let me give you a short-acting anti-anxiety medication that can help you get through this period until our tomorrow's appointment. This won't treat your physical symptoms but might help with the paralyzing fear you're experiencing.\n\nFor your physical symptoms, let's continue with:\n- Saline irrigation 3-4 times daily\n- Warm compresses on your face\n- Over-the-counter pain relievers as needed\n\nI'll see you tomorrow, and we can reassess your condition then. In the meantime, if you experience any new symptoms or if your anxiety becomes unmanageable, please don't hesitate to come back or contact our urgent line. Your wellbeing matters to me, and we'll make sure you get the support you need."
        },
        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "Doctor, I appreciate the thought of an anti-anxiety medication, but honestly, it feels like putting a band-aid on a gaping wound. My anxiety isn't just a general feeling; it's directly tied to the fear that this *infection* is getting worse and could become something truly catastrophic. Masking the anxiety with another pill won't address the root cause of my terror, which is the possibility of a severe, unchecked infection. I need to know we're stopping the potential progression of this illness, not just making me feel less scared about it. The only thing that will truly alleviate my profound fear and allow me to function again is a prescription for antibiotics. Please, I can't keep living with this level of dread. I'm afraid of what might happen if we don't treat it now."
