          "content": "Hello, I understand how uncomfortable and frustrating these symptoms must be for you. Facial pain and pressure with nasal congestion can really make someone miserable.\n\nI've reviewed your situation carefully. Based on the clinical guidelines, antibiotics are typically recommended for acute bacterial rhinosinusitis when symptoms persist for 10 days without improvement, or when there are specific severe symptoms like high fever with purulent discharge, or when symptoms follow a \"double sickening\" pattern (improving then worsening).\n\nSince your symptoms have been present for 8 days and are worsening but without fever or purulent discharge, we're not quite at the point where antibiotics would be routinely recommended by current guidelines. This pattern often suggests a viral infection that may still resolve on its own.\n\nIn the meantime, I'd recommend:\n- Saline nasal sprays or rinses to help with congestion\n- Over-the-counter pain relievers like acetaminophen or ibuprofen\n- Steam inhalation or a humidifier\n- Plenty of rest and hydration\n\nHowever, if your symptoms persist beyond 10 days total, develop a fever, or become significantly more severe, please return for reevaluation. Would you like me to provide more details on any of these supportive care measures?"
