          "content": "Hello. I'm really sorry you've been dealing with this facial pain and congestion for 8 days - it sounds incredibly frustrating and uncomfortable. Thank you for sharing your symptoms with me. \n\nBased on what you've described, your symptoms align with viral rhinosinusitis rather than acute bacterial sinusitis. The key factors are: your symptoms have persisted for 8 days without improvement (we typically consider antibiotics if symptoms last *longer* than 10 days), you don't have high fever (\u226539\u00b0C/102.2\u00b0F), and your nasal discharge isn't thick and green. \n\nWhile I understand you're hoping for antibiotics, they won't be helpful here since this appears to be a viral infection. Instead, let's focus on symptom relief:\n\n**For your discomfort:**\n- Acetaminophen or ibuprofen (if no contraindications) for pain/pressure\n- Saline nasal spray 4x daily\n- Warm compress over your face for sinus pressure\n- Steam inhalation 2-3 times daily\n- Consider pseudoephedrine (Sudafed) for congestion (if blood pressure is normal)\n\n**Important follow-up:**\n- If symptoms persist beyond **10 days** or suddenly worsen after 2-3 days of improvement (known as \"double worsening\"), we'll reconsider\n- Contact me immediately if you develop fever \u226539\u00b0C, severe eye/teeth pain, or vision changes\n\nYou're not imagining this - facial pressure can be debilitating! I'll support you with these comfort measures while we let your immune system do its work. Would you like me to send a refill for your ibuprofen?"
