          "content": "Hello, I'm glad you came in to discuss your symptoms. I understand how uncomfortable facial pain and pressure can be, especially when it's been going on for 8 days and seems to be getting worse.\n\nAfter reviewing your symptoms carefully, I notice that while you're experiencing facial pain and congestion, you don't have a fever, and your nasal discharge is clear or whitish rather than thick and colored. According to evidence-based guidelines, antibiotics are typically reserved for bacterial sinus infections, which would require either:\n\n- Symptoms lasting 10 days or more without improvement\n- Severe symptoms with high fever and purulent discharge for at least 3 days\n- A pattern of getting better then suddenly worse (\"double sickening\")\n\nYour case doesn't quite meet these criteria, suggesting this might be a viral infection that would typically resolve on its own. While I understand you were hoping for antibiotics, I'd recommend trying some self-care measures first that can help relieve your symptoms:\n\n- Saline nasal irrigation\n- Steam inhalation\n- Over-the-counter decongestants (used as directed)\n- Warm compresses on the face\n\nIf your symptoms don't improve in the next few days or worsen significantly, please return for follow-up. Would you like me to provide more details on any of these self-care approaches?"
