          "content": "I understand your frustration completely, and I can see why you'd want something to help with these worsening symptoms. You're right that it's been going on for a while and getting worse, which is certainly uncomfortable.\n\nHowever, based on current medical guidelines, antibiotics are specifically recommended for bacterial sinus infections that meet certain criteria - either lasting 10 days without improvement, severe symptoms with fever and purulent discharge, or the \"double sickening\" pattern of getting better then suddenly worse. Your case doesn't quite meet these criteria yet.\n\nThat said, this doesn't mean we can't help you feel better right now. There are several effective treatments we can try:\n\n- Saline nasal irrigation can reduce congestion and pressure\n- Decongestants (oral or nasal spray) for symptom relief\n- Pain relievers for the facial discomfort\n- Steam inhalation to help clear nasal passages\n\nIf your symptoms continue to worsen or don't improve in the next 2-3 days, I'd strongly recommend returning for reevaluation. At that point, we might need to reconsider treatment options.\n\nWould you like me to prescribe some of these alternative treatments to help manage your symptoms while we wait to see how things progress?"
