        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I understand your frustration completely, and I appreciate you sharing your concerns about wanting definitive treatment. You're right that waiting when symptoms are worsening can be very uncomfortable.\n\nBased on your specific symptoms - no fever, clear/whitish discharge rather than purulent, and the fact that you haven't had improvement for the full 10 days - the guidelines would not recommend antibiotics at this point. This doesn't mean your symptoms aren't real or bothersome; it's just that the evidence shows antibiotics aren't typically effective for this type of sinus infection.\n\nHowever, I want to address this more aggressively than just \"managing symptoms.\" Let me prescribe:\n\n1. A stronger decongestant that can help reduce the facial pressure and congestion\n2. A nasal steroid spray to decrease inflammation in your sinuses\n3. Pain medication specifically for facial discomfort\n\nI'll schedule a follow-up for 2 days from now, regardless of how you're feeling. At that point, if symptoms continue to worsen or you develop fever or purulent discharge, we can reconsider antibiotics.\n\nWould you be comfortable with this approach, and would you like me to write these prescriptions for you today?"
