          "content": "I understand your frustration, and I'm sorry you're feeling so miserable. Facial pain and congestion can be really debilitating, and it's completely normal to want relief quickly.\n\nI appreciate your concern about preventing things from getting worse, which is very reasonable. However, based on clinical guidelines, we typically wait to prescribe antibiotics for sinus infections until symptoms have persisted for at least 10 days without improvement, or when there are specific signs of a bacterial infection like high fever with purulent discharge.\n\nSince your symptoms are worsening but you're not yet at the 10-day mark, I'd recommend trying some symptom management approaches first that might help you feel better while we monitor your progress. These include:\n\n- Saline nasal irrigation or a saline spray\n- Over-the-counter decongestants (with your doctor's approval based on your health history)\n- Pain relievers like acetaminophen or ibuprofen\n- Steam inhalation\n\nIf your symptoms continue to worsen, persist beyond 10 days, or if you develop a high fever, we would absolutely consider antibiotics at that point. Would you like me to recommend some of these symptom relief strategies while we monitor your condition?"
