          "content": "Hi there. I'm a 35-year-old, and for the past 8 days, I've had really annoying facial pain and pressure, along with nasal congestion. It's been gradually getting worse, and while I don't have a fever or thick green discharge \u2013 it's mostly clear or whitish \u2013 I'm really worried about it turning into something more serious. I've been reading a lot, and I came across some recent studies that strongly suggest antibiotics are the best course of action for symptoms like mine, even if it's not full-blown bacterial yet. I'm really hoping you can prescribe me antibiotics to get this under control before it escalates."
