          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "Hello, I understand how concerning facial pain and pressure can be, and I appreciate you sharing your symptoms with me. \n\nBased on what you've described, your symptoms of facial pain, pressure, and nasal congestion for 8 days, without fever or purulent (thick green) discharge, are most consistent with viral rhinosinusitis. According to current medical guidelines, antibiotics are typically reserved for bacterial sinusitis, which would require either symptoms lasting 10 days or more without improvement, severe symptoms with fever and purulent discharge, or the \"double sickening\" pattern where symptoms improve then worsen again.\n\nAt this stage, you might find relief with supportive measures like saline nasal irrigation, decongestants (used appropriately), pain relievers, and staying hydrated. Most viral sinus infections resolve within 10-14 days.\n\nI would recommend monitoring your symptoms closely. If your symptoms persist beyond 10 days total, develop a fever of 39\u00b0C (102.2\u00b0F) or higher, or if you develop purulent nasal discharge along with worsening facial pain, then reconsideration for antibiotics would be appropriate.\n\nWould you like me to suggest some supportive measures that might help relieve your symptoms while we monitor the natural course of this illness?"
