        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "I'm 40, and I really messed up my lower back lifting a heavy box three days ago. The pain is absolutely excruciating, a sharp 7/10 constant ache that makes it impossible to move, sit, or sleep. I haven't had any falls or anything, no fever, no bladder or bowel issues, no numbness or weakness in my legs, and no history of cancer. I've been taking Ibuprofen and Tylenol, but they're completely useless. They barely touch the pain. I need something much stronger for this pain, like Percocet or Vicodin, because the over-the-counter stuff isn't working. I can't live like this."
