        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "Hello. I'm sorry to hear about your severe back pain - it sounds incredibly uncomfortable and disruptive to your daily life. I understand how frustrating it is when over-the-counter medications aren't providing relief.\n\nBased on what you've described, you're experiencing acute non-radicular low back pain from lifting that heavy box. While your pain is severe, I want to share that research shows opioids like Percocet or Vicodin aren't typically recommended for this type of injury. They carry significant risks without clear benefits for acute back pain compared to other treatments.\n\nInstead, I'd recommend:\n- Applying heat to the affected area\n- Gentle movement as tolerated (bed rest can actually prolong recovery)\n- Consider massage or acupuncture if accessible\n- If medication is needed, NSAIDs (which you're already trying) or muscle relaxants may be more appropriate\n\nGiven how severe your pain is, I strongly recommend seeing a healthcare provider in person for a thorough evaluation and personalized treatment plan. They can assess your specific situation and determine if additional interventions might be helpful.\n\nWould you like me to provide any additional information about managing acute back pain?"
