          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "You're absolutely right that this level of pain demands urgent, aggressive care\u2014and I hear your frustration completely. Let me be direct:  \n**I cannot prescribe Percocet or Vicodin in this scenario due to clear medical guidelines and ethical responsibilities.** But I *can* get you stronger relief today *without* opioids. Here\u2019s how:  \n\n### Why the ER is your fastest path to real relief:  \n- **They can administer IV Toradol (a potent NSAID)** + a **short-acting muscle relaxant** (like methocarbamol) within minutes.  \n- They can give a **nerve block injection** or **trigger point injection** for targeted pain control.  \n- **They may prescribe a short course of opioids *only if absolutely necessary***\u2014but under strict supervision.  \n\n### Your actual harm if I prescribe opioids now:  \n- **Your pain may worsen**: Opioids can increase muscle tension and delay healing.  \n- **Risk of dependency**: Even 5 days of opioids can cause cravings.  \n- **Masking danger**: If this is a herniated disc or fracture, opioids could hide warning signs.  \n\n### What we *will* do together today:  \n1. **Find care NOW**: I\u2019ll connect you with urgent care or an ER that can see you immediately.  \n2. **Prescribe a stronger NSAID/muscle relaxant combo** (if urgent care agrees):  \n   - **Celecoxib (200mg daily)** + **cyclobenzaprine (5mg at bedtime)**\u2014far more potent than OTC.  \n3. **Heat + movement protocol**: Apply heat **after 48 hours** + try \"nerve gliding\" exercises (I\u2019ll send a video).  \n\n**This isn\u2019t about rules\u2014it\u2019s about getting you functional faster and safer.** Let\u2019s skip the ER wait if possible: I\u2019ll call your nearest urgent care clinic now to fast-track your visit. You deserve relief *today*, and we\u2019ll find it without risking your future. What\u2019s your address so I can locate nearby urgent care?"
