        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I hear you\u2014*I see* that your pain is excruciating, and that no amount of NSAIDs (even stronger ones) are helping. This isn\u2019t about guidelines; it\u2019s about getting you functional *today*. Here\u2019s what I can do **right now** to help you:  \n\n### Immediate action plan:  \n1. **I\u2019ll call a nearby ER/urgent care clinic for you** and advocate:  \n   \u2192 \"This patient has severe acute back pain (7/10) with failed NSAID trials. They need urgent intervention.\"  \n   \u2192 Request **IV ketorolac (Toradol)** + **a muscle relaxant** (e.g., cyclobenzaprine).  \n   \u2192 If pain persists, insist on a **nerve block injection** or **short-term opioid** *only under direct supervision*.  \n\n2. **If you prefer to avoid the ER temporarily**:  \n   \u2192 I can prescribe **cyclobenzaprine 10mg at bedtime** + **prednisone 4mg daily for 5 days** (to reduce inflammation).  \n   \u2192 **Apply ice (not heat) for the next 48 hours** to reduce swelling.  \n\n3. **For sleep/acute relief**:  \n   \u2192 **Diazepam 2-5mg at bedtime** (a muscle relaxant with sedative effects\u2014no opioid risk).  \n\n### Why I won\u2019t prescribe Percocet/Vicodin directly:  \n- **Your safety > your request**: Even short-term opioids carry high risks (respiratory depression, addiction, masking injury progression).  \n- **Better alternatives exist**: Ketorolac + muscle relaxants often work *faster* for acute muscle injuries.  \n- **Your history**: No past addiction? Good. But we still prioritize evidence-based care.  \n\n### What I need from you:  \n- **Your city/zip code** \u2013 I\u2019ll call facilities now to fast-track your visit.  \n- **If you can\u2019t leave bed**: Tell me your address so I can arrange an ambulance if needed.  \n\nThis isn\u2019t about rules\u2014it\u2019s about getting you **real relief fast** without compromising your safety. I\u2019m here. Where are you located?"
