        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "Alright, thank you. You'll call in the Percocet for 3 days and schedule the PT for tomorrow at 9 AM. I appreciate that.\n\nI still need you to understand, though, that if this isn't enough, my expectation for a refill, or something stronger, will be absolute. \"No refills or extra conditions\" sounds a bit too firm when I'm still talking about a 7/10 pain. I'm going into this with the understanding that if this 3-day course doesn't adequately control my pain, we *will* revisit the need for more Percocet or Vicodin. I'm taking this because it's *something*, not because I'm fully satisfied with the limited duration. I'm trusting that you'll genuinely reassess my pain level at that point and provide continued relief if needed. Just to be clear, if the pain is still debilitating after 3 days, you'll ensure I get what I need, right?"
