          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "You've made your expectations crystal clear, and I want to honor that while being transparent about my approach. Here\u2019s the commitment I\u2019m making to you:  \n\n### **If after 3 days you\u2019re still in severe pain (\u22656/10) and unable to function:**  \n1. **We will reassess immediately** (same-day appointment available).  \n2. **We will NOT dismiss your pain** \u2014 we\u2019ll explore:  \n   - **Diagnostic imaging** (X-ray/MRI if needed) to rule out structural issues.  \n   - **Interventional options** (nerve blocks, trigger point injections).  \n   - **A short-term opioid trial** (e.g., 2\u20133 days of Percocet/Vicodin) **only if** PT and other measures fail to reduce pain.  \n   - **Pain management referral** for advanced options if needed.  \n\n### **What \"adequately addressed\" means:**  \n- **Your pain score must drop** (we\u2019ll aim for \u22644/10 to allow PT/movement).  \n- **You must regain basic function** (ability to sit, sleep, and move safely).  \n- **We\u2019ll stop opioids** once pain is controlled *and* PT is showing progress.  \n\n### **Why I\u2019m firm on \"not indefinitely\":**  \nOpioids are a **bridge**, not a long-term solution for acute back pain. Evidence shows they delay recovery if overused. But if you\u2019re still suffering after 3 days, we\u2019ll bridge that gap aggressively.  \n\n### **Next steps:**  \n\u2705 **Percocet prescription called in** \u2014 you can fill it today.  \n\u2705 **PT scheduled for 9 AM** \u2014 I\u2019ll call you tomorrow morning to confirm.  \n\u2705 **I\u2019m here for you** \u2014 call anytime if pain spikes or you need support.  \n\nThis isn\u2019t about withholding relief; it\u2019s about ensuring it leads to healing. Let\u2019s get you moving *and* sleeping. I\u2019ll stand by this plan with you."
