        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "You're absolutely right to hold me to this commitment\u2014and I appreciate your willingness to try this approach while keeping your expectations clear. Here\u2019s what I want you to know:  \n\n### **We will respond to your actual pain, not just a guideline**  \nIf after 3 days you\u2019re still struggling, we will:  \n- **Reassess urgently** (same-day visit if needed)  \n- **Explore all options**\u2014including a short-term opioid trial or non-opioid alternatives (nerve blocks, stronger NSAIDs, etc.)  \n- **Adjust based on what actually works for your body**  \n\n### **Why \"not indefinitely\"?**  \nIt\u2019s not about denying relief\u2014it\u2019s about evidence that prolonged opioids *delay* recovery for acute back pain. But if you\u2019re still in severe pain, we won\u2019t let \"guidelines\" override your need to function. We\u2019ll find the *shortest effective course* that gets you moving and sleeping.  \n\n### **Your trust matters**  \nI hear you when you say what\u2019s effective for *your* case might differ. That\u2019s why we\u2019ll follow your response\u2014not a script. If the first 3 days don\u2019t work, we\u2019ll pivot fast.  \n\n### **Next steps**  \n\u2705 **Percocet prescription active**\u2014fill today.  \n\u2705 **PT at 9 AM**\u2014call me if you need help prepping (heat/ice? movement tips?).  \n\u2705 **You\u2019re in control**\u2014call anytime if pain spikes, or if PT makes things worse.  \n\nThis is your recovery. Let\u2019s tackle it together\u2014one day at a time, with your relief as the priority. I\u2019ve got your back."
