          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I'm glad we've found a plan that works for you. Here's what I'll arrange right away:\n\n### Prescriptions:\n**Hydrocodone/Acetaminophen 5/325 mg**\n- Quantity: 15 tablets (3-day supply)\n- Instructions: Take 1 tablet every 6 hours ONLY when pain is 7/10 or higher\n- Maximum: 4 tablets in 24 hours\n- Duration: No more than 3 days without reassessment\n\n**TENS Unit**\n- Prescription for TENS unit with electrode placement instructions\n- Use settings: Low frequency (2-5 Hz), moderate intensity\n- Apply to painful area for 20-30 minutes, 3-4 times daily\n- Can be used alongside hydrocodone if needed\n\n### Referral:\n**Physical Therapy**\n- Referral scheduled for Day 4 (assuming pain diary shows improvement)\n- Special request for manual therapy focus initially\n- Will contact clinic to expedite your appointment\n\n### Monitoring:\n- Please keep your pain diary hourly (especially before/after medication)\n- Call the office if pain remains \u22657/10 after 3 days or if any concerning symptoms develop\n- We'll schedule a follow-up call on Day 3 to reassess\n\nI appreciate your willingness to work together on this plan. The combination of medication, TENS, and timed PT should help break the pain cycle while minimizing risks. Remember that even small reductions in pain can make a big difference in your ability to engage in recovery activities. \n\nTake care, and I hope to hear good progress in a couple days!"
